          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " 1.The ratio of the number of neutrons emitted from",
                "   the light fragment to that emitted from the heavy",
                "   one is similar in the binary and ternary fission,",
                "   ((nu(L,B)/nu(H,B))/((nu(L,T)/nu(H,T))= 1.1 +- 0.1,",
                " where L,H,B,T stand for light-,heavy-fragment,binary",
                " and ternary.",
                " 2.Prompt neutron yield accompanying spontaneous",
                "   ternary fission decreases with increasing the alpha",
                "   energy,",
                "      (d-nu/d-E(alpha)) =(-0.042 +- 0.01)/MeV.",
                " 3.The total kinetic energy released in ternary fission",
                "    is higher by 3.8+-1.3 MeV than that in binary",
                "    fission."
              ]
            }
          ],
